Arithematic Progression:
1) nth term - an = a1+(n-1)d
2) when we need to find two terms an = am + (n-m)d
3) sum of n terms = (n/2)+(2a+(n-1)d)
Geometric Progression:
1) nth term : ar^(n-1)
2) sum of n terms : a(r^(n-1)-1)/(r-1)
3) sum of infinite terms : a/1-r
Harmonic mean:
1) nth term : 1/(a+(n-1)d)
2) sum of n terms : 1/d(ln[2a+(n-1)d/(2a-d)])
